---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '@components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Peak Pomodoro — Support"
  description="Support and FAQs for Peak Pomodoro, the climb-a-mountain Pomodoro timer from Northland Studios."
>
  <Nav />

  <main id="main">
    <header class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero-inner">
        <div class="mono label">§ Peak Pomodoro</div>
        <h1>Support</h1>
        <p class="lede">A climb-a-mountain Pomodoro focus timer. iPhone + Apple Watch. Free, no ads, no tracking.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section narrow">
      <div class="mono label">§ Quick links</div>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/peak-pomodoro/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <div class="mono label">§ FAQ</div>

      <h3>How does the climbing metaphor work?</h3>
      <p>Each 25-minute focus session is a step up the active mountain. Whitney is unlocked from day one. Denali unlocks at 10 completed sessions, Kilimanjaro at 25, Everest at 50. Your climber's vertical progress on the timer face reflects the current week's progress.</p>

      <h3>Why does Peak Pomodoro ask for HealthKit access?</h3>
      <p>If you grant it, each completed focus session writes to Apple Health as a Mindful Minutes entry — so your focus time shows up next to your meditation and other mindful activities. If you deny, the app works exactly the same; the only thing missing is the Health write-back. You can change this any time in Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security &rarr; Health.</p>

      <h3>Does it sync between my iPhone and Apple Watch?</h3>
      <p>Yes. The watch app mirrors the phone timer in real time. Stats also sync across all your iCloud-signed-in devices via Apple's private key-value store. There's no Northland account to create.</p>

      <h3>Why is the Live Activity sometimes 1 second off?</h3>
      <p>iOS's Live Activity engine snapshots state on a slight delay when you return from background. As of Build 25 the app re-anchors to wall-clock time on every foreground event, so any drift resolves within ~1 second.</p>

      <h3>What's the tip jar?</h3>
      <p>Three optional one-time in-app purchases — Base Camp ($2.99), Summit ($4.99), Everest ($9.99). They unlock a cosmetic supporter badge in the About section and nothing else. Peak Pomodoro is free in full, forever; the tip jar exists only for people who want to throw something in the hat. No paywalls, no gated peaks, no removed ads.</p>

      <h3>How do I delete my data?</h3>
      <p>Uninstall the app. All app data is on-device or in your private iCloud key-value store. For HealthKit data: <em>Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security &rarr; Health &rarr; Peak Pomodoro &rarr; Delete All Data</em>. For iCloud KV data: <em>Settings &rarr; Apple ID &rarr; iCloud &rarr; Manage Account Storage</em>.</p>

      <h3>How do I report a bug or request a feature?</h3>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a> with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your iOS version (Settings &rarr; General &rarr; About &rarr; iOS Version)</li>
        <li>Your device model</li>
        <li>Steps to reproduce, if a bug</li>
        <li>A screenshot if it helps</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I read every message and usually reply within 48 hours.</p>

      <h3>Is there an iPad / Mac / web version?</h3>
      <p>Not yet. v1.0 is iPhone + Apple Watch only. iPad support is on the v1.x roadmap.</p>

      <div class="mono label">§ Known issues</div>
      <p>None currently. This section will be updated per release as real-user reports come in.</p>

      <div class="mono label">§ Contact</div>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a> — usually replies within 48 hours, often same day.
      </p>

      <p class="back">
        <em>Peak Pomodoro is made by Northland Studios.</em>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--bg-soft); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .page-hero-inner { max-width: var(--col-narrow); margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(60px, 10vh, 100px) var(--pad-page); }
  .page-hero .label { color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 14px 0; }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
    margin: 0 0 22px 0;
  }
  .page-hero .lede {
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .section.narrow { padding-top: clamp(50px, 6vh, 80px); padding-bottom: clamp(50px, 6vh, 80px); max-width: var(--col-narrow); margin: 0 auto; padding-left: var(--pad-page); padding-right: var(--pad-page); }
  .section .label { color: var(--accent); margin: 36px 0 12px 0; }
  .section .label:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .section p, .section ul {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.66;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 18px 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 22px 0 8px 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .section ul { padding-left: 22px; }
  .section li { margin: 0 0 8px 0; }
  .section a { color: var(--accent); }
  .section .back { margin-top: 36px; color: var(--ink-muted); }
</style>
